    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="188"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/5–2648:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret   us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-26T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 26, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1812. Personal for <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName>. Re French
                    suggested debate of German program by Assembly Foreign Affairs Committee
                        (<persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName>’ 232 to you<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d188fn1">Same as telegram 2271, <gloss target="#t_Delsec1"
                            >Delsec</gloss> 1754, May 25, from London, <ref target="#pg_280">p.
                            280</ref>.</note>) we can conceive of nothing that would more
                    effectively destroy basis of conference if such debate took place before
                    agreement at London and we assume French will have perception to abandon any
                    such idea. Pls advise to what extent London agreement if reached will require
                    Assembly approval before announcement of final French Govt approval and your
                    estimate of effect such debate, if any, on implementation of program.</p>
                <p>Repeated to London as <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1924.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
